Pronunciation: 'rü-m&amp;r<br>
Function: noun<br>
Etymology: Middle English rumour, from Middle French, from Latin rumor clamor, gossip; akin to Old English rEon to lament, Sanskrit rauti he roars<br>
Date: 14th century<br>
1 : talk or opinion widely disseminated with no discernible source<br>
2 : a statement or report current without known authority for its truth<br>
3 archaic : talk or report of a notable person or event<br>
4 : a soft low indistinct sound : MURMUR <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  The rumors swirling around now are just that. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Using the above definition (which is from www.merriam-webster.com), this statement means the same as 'We haven't and aren't saying anything about this.'<br>
<br>
Imho, why do they talk about the delay rumor without any mention of the more dreaded one about locking out european players from american servers. Personally I will assume this is spin control and get my copy from the US. Unless VI specifically speak out against it, I'm not taking any chances. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=navnloes>Navnloes</A> at: 10/1/02 4:58:26 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern>The Nameless Tavern</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion>General Discussion</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
